  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice your<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604317529794-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604317529794-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604317529794-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604317529794-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604317529794-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two)</p><p>Sprinkle 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> over the bacon</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the other side of the tray[s] and drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the bacon is golden and the tomatoes have softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604317534014-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604317534014-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604317534014-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604317534014-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604317534014-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and<strong> onion marmalade</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until thickened<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>easy balsamic ketchup</strong></p><p>Once done, set aside to cool</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604317543551-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604317543551-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604317543551-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604317543551-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604317543551-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the ketchup is done, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a large bowl and add 130ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[190ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and whisk everything together until smooth – this is your <strong>cheesy mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
